qas.question: Which street is a pedestrian plaza between Third Avenue and Lexington Avenue?
Which park is at the end of 24th Street and Madison Avenue?
After being interrupted, where do 24th and 25th Streets continue from?

context: 24th Street is in two parts. 24th Street starts at <a1_0>First Avenue<a1_0/> and it ends at Madison Avenue, because of <a2_0>Madison Square Park<a2_0/>. <a0_0>25th Street<a0_0/>, which is in three parts, starts at FDR Drive, is a pedestrian plaza between Third Avenue and Lexington Avenue, and ends at <a3_0>Madison<a3_0/>. Then West 24th and 25th Streets continue from <a4_0>Fifth Avenue<a4_0/> to Eleventh Avenue (25th) or Twelfth Avenue (24th).
